<i> And after "As the Bell Rings,"</i>

13:09.888 --> 13:11.590
I booked "Camp Rock."

13:11.623 --> 13:13.926
<i> I was 15.</i>

13:13.958 --> 13:14.926
Rock on.

13:14.960 --> 13:16.595
<i> When I met Phil,</i>

13:16.628 --> 13:18.363
he was managing
the Jonas Brothers.

13:18.395 --> 13:19.897
Joe Jonas: <i>
 We met Demi, I think,</i>

13:19.931 --> 13:20.899
<i> originally it was an audition</i>

13:20.932 --> 13:22.967
of our TV show.

13:23.000 --> 13:25.269
<i> We had a TV show
 called "Jonas."</i>

13:25.302 --> 13:27.038
She didn't get it, but...

13:27.072 --> 13:30.174
- ( laughter )
- we...

13:30.207 --> 13:34.212
<i> I think a year later, I think
 we met in rehearsals probably
 for "Camp Rock."</i>

13:34.245 --> 13:36.848
-<i> Demi was attached
 to the film already. </i>
-<i> And I remember</i>

13:36.881 --> 13:38.382
you went in 'cause you
had to sing the duet

13:38.416 --> 13:40.219
<i> with Demi's character.</i>

13:40.251 --> 13:41.452
You had already
laid down your part.

13:41.485 --> 13:43.388
- Mm-hmm.
- I went in with Joe,

13:43.421 --> 13:46.057
and I heard her voice,
I just had, like, goose bumps

13:46.091 --> 13:48.226
all over my arms.

13:48.259 --> 13:50.528
I was like-- I stepped out of
the studio and I called Disney,
I was like,

13:50.562 --> 13:51.996
<i> "Who is this girl?"</i>

13:54.231 --> 13:56.334
I saw what he did
for the Jonas Brothers,

13:56.368 --> 13:59.538
<i> and the fact that he wanted to
manage me was a huge deal to me</i>

13:59.571 --> 14:03.875
<i> because he was with them
 through it all.</i>

14:03.908 --> 14:06.912
Starring in "Camp Rock"
was Demi's big break.

14:06.945 --> 14:10.215
<i>It was just a massive franchise
 that Disney had put</i>

14:10.248 --> 14:12.350
<i> everything behind.</i>

14:12.384 --> 14:14.418
<i> And it just became
 a pop culture,</i>

14:14.451 --> 14:15.921
sort of, sensation.

14:15.953 --> 14:17.088
To be able to

14:17.121 --> 14:18.089
<i> get to do something</i>

14:18.123 --> 14:19.424
<i> as big as this,</i>

14:19.456 --> 14:20.893
<i> um, for my first project,</i>

14:20.926 --> 14:22.261
it feels good.

14:22.293 --> 14:23.995
We really believed
that "Camp Rock"

14:24.028 --> 14:27.099
<i> was the vehicle to become
 a superstar.</i>

14:27.131 --> 14:29.901
And it was like overnight,
she became a household name.

14:29.934 --> 14:32.570
<i> ( music playing )</i>

14:42.647 --> 14:44.182
<i> I think Demi</i>

14:44.215 --> 14:47.152
was cast in so many different
Disney projects

14:47.184 --> 14:51.122
<i> because there was
 a natural edge to her</i>

14:51.155 --> 14:54.625
<i> that made her... authentic</i>

14:54.658 --> 14:55.660
<i> and believable</i>

14:55.693 --> 14:58.229
as an actress or as an artist.

14:58.263 --> 15:00.331
<i> I think they needed her</i>

15:00.365 --> 15:04.369
<i> to make their projects cooler.</i>

15:04.402 --> 15:05.937
Demi: <i>
 Everything happened</i>

15:05.971 --> 15:07.072
so fast.

15:07.105 --> 15:09.541
We officially signed,

15:09.573 --> 15:11.709
<i> and the next day,
 I booked her a plane ticket</i>

15:11.743 --> 15:13.512
<i> to go on tour
 with the Jonas Brothers.</i>

15:13.544 --> 15:15.313
( cheering and applause )

15:17.615 --> 15:18.616
<i> All of a sudden,</i>

15:18.649 --> 15:19.650
<i> I was on tour,</i>

15:19.683 --> 15:20.651
<i> writing songs for my album</i>

15:20.684 --> 15:23.020
<i> with the Jonas Brothers.</i>

15:23.053 --> 15:25.456
<i> And then I was on
 a tour of my own.</i>

15:27.759 --> 15:30.495
<i> Looking back,
 I think that it was a lot</i>

15:30.528 --> 15:32.965
for anyone, let alone,

15:32.998 --> 15:36.100
<i> a kid.</i>

15:36.134 --> 15:39.270
I think that Demi
being on the Disney Channel,

15:39.303 --> 15:41.305
now looking back at it,
I can connect the dots

15:41.339 --> 15:43.208
and say that there was an
immense amount of pressure.

15:44.775 --> 15:47.245
<i> I was now working on my music,</i>

15:47.278 --> 15:51.416
<i> and my TV show and movies</i>

15:51.448 --> 15:53.051
all at the same time.

15:54.619 --> 15:55.754
<i> That lifestyle's really crazy.</i>

15:55.787 --> 15:57.522
Not a lot of people understand,

15:57.554 --> 15:59.357
like, the pressures,
and the time,

15:59.390 --> 16:01.692
<i> and the amount of work
 that it actually takes</i>

16:01.725 --> 16:04.428
<i> to have such
 a successful career</i>

16:04.461 --> 16:05.563
in the entertainment industry.

16:07.532 --> 16:09.167
<i> So many more expectations</i>

16:09.200 --> 16:13.072
put on her than a normal
15, 16-year-old girl would have.

16:15.572 --> 16:17.375
Phil: <i>
 She was living two lives.</i>

16:17.408 --> 16:19.510
Here she was,
she had to be squeaky clean

16:19.543 --> 16:21.579
on the Disney Channel,

16:21.613 --> 16:23.482
<i> all types of moral clauses</i>

16:23.514 --> 16:25.384
<i> and just intensity around</i>

16:25.417 --> 16:28.687
behavior, and,
once the camera stops rolling,

16:28.720 --> 16:31.723
<i> she's living another life;
she couldn't really be herself.</i>

16:31.755 --> 16:33.692
She couldn't be
a normal teenager.

16:36.226 --> 16:37.361
<i> I definitely felt</i>

16:37.394 --> 16:41.600
the pressure increase when...

16:41.633 --> 16:44.636
<i> the fame started to
 creep into my life.</i>

16:44.668 --> 16:46.704
<i> I started feeling pressured to</i>

16:46.738 --> 16:49.241
<i> look a certain way, to...</i>

16:49.274 --> 16:51.243
<i> sing music that I felt</i>

16:51.275 --> 16:53.144
people would like,

16:53.177 --> 16:55.379
rather than sing music
that I would like.

16:55.413 --> 16:58.450
<i> There was more pressure
 to succeed, you know?</i>

16:58.482 --> 17:00.084
<i> Numbers and charts.</i>

17:00.118 --> 17:02.153
And I was a perfectionist,

17:02.187 --> 17:04.088
and I really wanted to be
the best of the best.

17:04.122 --> 17:06.590
<i> ( music playing )</i>

17:06.624 --> 17:09.260
Phil: <i>
 When you are carrying
 a franchise,</i>

17:09.294 --> 17:13.165
there is a standard
that everybody expects
you to operate at.

17:13.198 --> 17:15.333
They were great to work with.

17:15.365 --> 17:16.567
Awful, awful.

17:16.601 --> 17:17.636
<i> I think it caused</i>

17:17.669 --> 17:20.472
a lot of, um, anxiety for her.

17:20.505 --> 17:23.642
Demi: <i>
 And it didn't let up
 at all, it just...</i>

17:23.674 --> 17:25.509
<i> mounted more and more.</i>

17:25.541 --> 17:27.344
<i> All of a sudden,
 she had to be</i>

17:27.377 --> 17:29.548
this role model, and I don't
think she was ready for that.

17:31.548 --> 17:32.850
<i> I think we started to notice,</i>

17:32.884 --> 17:34.586
and, really,
it was the Jonas Brothers

17:34.618 --> 17:36.320
kind of, like,
waving a flag that

17:36.354 --> 17:37.823
Demi may be veering

17:37.855 --> 17:40.659
<i> off the path.</i>

17:40.692 --> 17:41.859
<i> At that point,
 you could just feel</i>

17:41.893 --> 17:45.663
that... things were
getting wobbly.

17:45.696 --> 17:50.468
<i> It was almost like the wheels
 were starting to fall off.</i>

17:50.501 --> 17:53.771
<i> Prior to that, I think,
 anything that was going on,</i>

17:53.805 --> 17:55.340
<i> would've been chalked up to...</i>

17:55.373 --> 17:57.709
<i> she's a teenage girl.</i>

17:57.741 --> 18:00.111
<i> That was, like,
 the easy answer,</i>

18:00.144 --> 18:02.346
was just to say,
"Well, she's a teenage girl

18:02.380 --> 18:03.381
and she's going through stuff,

18:03.413 --> 18:05.750
<i> and she's being dramatic."</i>

18:05.782 --> 18:08.385
John: <i>
 She wasn't this sweet
 and lovely girl anymore,</i>

18:08.419 --> 18:10.122
<i>and it was kind of like a "Hey,</i>

18:10.154 --> 18:11.889
<i> ( bleep ) you."
 And, "I just want to be a kid</i>

18:11.923 --> 18:14.759
and do what everybody else does.
And, like, my friends in Texas

18:14.791 --> 18:17.628
<i>want to, like, drink and party,
 so why shouldn't I
 drink and party?"</i>

18:19.463 --> 18:21.700
Phil: <i>
 Demi had real anger issues.</i>

18:24.769 --> 18:27.271
John: <i>
Difficult, harder to be around.</i>

18:27.305 --> 18:29.541
No, no, no, just show me,
I have a photographic memory.

18:29.574 --> 18:31.543
<i> Demi's pulling anyone
 that she could, like,</i>

18:31.576 --> 18:34.278
<i> manipulate and change.</i>

18:34.311 --> 18:38.182
Phil: <i>
 She was depressed,
 she would sleep all the time.</i>

18:38.215 --> 18:42.286
I think she just--
it became obvious that
she was struggling with...

18:42.319 --> 18:44.855
<i> herself.</i>

18:44.888 --> 18:47.391
And I didn't realize that it was
actually signaling

18:47.424 --> 18:49.394
<i> a larger issue.</i>

18:51.563 --> 18:53.365
Nick Jonas: <i>
 While we were on tour,</i>

18:53.397 --> 18:56.400
Joe and Demi's relationship
had become really complicated.

18:56.433 --> 18:58.603
<i> So I was playing the bridge.</i>

18:58.635 --> 18:59.637
<i> And it became really good,</i>

18:59.671 --> 19:02.474
you know, between she and I

19:02.507 --> 19:06.644
<i>for a while, and growing closer
 than we'd ever been.</i>

19:06.678 --> 19:08.380
And I remember thinking
in my head,

19:08.413 --> 19:10.448
I felt, like,
a bit of pride about it,

19:10.480 --> 19:13.684
like... selfishly, maybe.
I was like,

19:13.718 --> 19:15.653
"I'm helping her back into,
you know, 

19:15.686 --> 19:18.222
<i> coming back to being the Demi
 that we all know and love,</i>

19:18.256 --> 19:19.891
<i>and she's not gonna do anything
 crazy, it's gonna be fine."</i>

19:19.923 --> 19:21.759
And then this episode happened.

19:21.792 --> 19:24.395
<i> ( music playing )</i>

19:28.932 --> 19:30.835
Demi: <i>
 I was in Colombia.</i>

19:30.867 --> 19:33.270
I was on
the "Camp Rock 2" Tour.

19:33.304 --> 19:37.375
<i> And I invited a bunch of
 people to dinner,</i>

19:37.407 --> 19:39.310
<i> my band,</i>

19:39.344 --> 19:42.581
and my background dancers.

19:42.614 --> 19:44.481
I paid for all the alcohol.

19:44.515 --> 19:45.884
<i> Somebody ended up</i>

19:45.916 --> 19:48.220
getting weed.

19:48.252 --> 19:49.486
I was on Adderall.

19:49.519 --> 19:51.623
<i> And...</i>

19:51.655 --> 19:52.957
we had trashed the hotel.

19:52.990 --> 19:56.228
<i> The hotel was,
 like, threatening us.</i>

19:56.260 --> 19:58.495
They went to some of the dancers
and asked what had happened.

19:58.528 --> 20:00.598
<i> And I think they told</i>

20:00.632 --> 20:02.901
on me for using Adderall.

20:05.369 --> 20:07.871
Somebody told Kevin Jonas, Sr.,

20:07.904 --> 20:10.341
<i> and... Phil.</i>

20:10.375 --> 20:13.612
and my dad.

20:13.644 --> 20:16.013
I was very upset.

20:16.047 --> 20:18.717
<i> I couldn't believe
 what had happened.</i>

20:18.750 --> 20:19.951
<i> Now it was out</i>

20:19.983 --> 20:21.653
that I was on Adderall.

20:23.654 --> 20:24.990
The next day,

20:25.022 --> 20:28.459
<i> I was in a lot of trouble.</i>

20:28.492 --> 20:31.829
I remember...

20:31.863 --> 20:33.431
going to Kevin, Sr.
and saying,

20:33.463 --> 20:35.532
<i> "Listen...</i>

20:35.566 --> 20:38.502
I want to thank whoever
told on me because

20:38.536 --> 20:41.972
<i> I know they were
 just worried about me.</i>

20:42.006 --> 20:44.875
<i> And, you know, I just really
 want to know who told you."</i>

20:44.909 --> 20:48.513
And I manipulated him
into telling me who it was.

20:48.546 --> 20:50.715
And he said it was Shorty.

20:50.748 --> 20:53.884
<i> Shorty and I
 had been really close</i>

20:53.917 --> 20:56.787
<i> through "Camp Rock"
 and "Camp Rock 2."</i>

20:56.820 --> 20:57.955
<i> So...</i>

20:57.989 --> 20:59.923
<i> when he said Shorty,</i>

20:59.957 --> 21:01.893
I remember thinking...

21:01.925 --> 21:05.062
"I'm about to
beat this bitch up."

21:05.096 --> 21:08.333
<i> ( music playing )</i>

21:08.365 --> 21:09.968
John: <i>
 I remember I was up in
 the front of the plane.</i>

21:10.000 --> 21:11.735
She had already
boarded the plane.

21:11.769 --> 21:14.005
John: <i>
 Demi walks up
 onto the plane and</i>

21:14.038 --> 21:15.006
I heard some commotion.

21:15.038 --> 21:16.540
I just went up to her.

21:18.576 --> 21:20.644
- And it was like a blur.
- I turned around and Demi had

21:20.678 --> 21:23.048
punched her backup dancer
in the face.

21:23.080 --> 21:24.782
Everyone was freaking out.

21:24.816 --> 21:27.318
She walked right past me
without acknowledging me.

21:27.352 --> 21:29.387
I just remember
going and sitting down.

21:29.420 --> 21:31.389
Just this angry
look on her face.

21:31.422 --> 21:32.824
Texting my mom "I'm sorry."

21:32.856 --> 21:34.459
Put her head on her pillow

21:34.491 --> 21:36.327
and shut out the world.

21:36.361 --> 21:40.065
And I slept the whole day.

21:40.097 --> 21:42.866
That was when
it dawned on me that

21:42.900 --> 21:44.869
this was probably a much bigger

21:44.902 --> 21:48.440
situation than just a kid
who wanted to party.

21:52.743 --> 21:53.845
I just came to a breaking point.

21:56.980 --> 22:00.518
<i> ( music playing )</i>

22:00.550 --> 22:01.752
Phil: <i>
 The next 12 months</i>

22:01.786 --> 22:02.854
<i> were extremely difficult.</i>

22:07.458 --> 22:09.928
Demi: <i>
 I was 18 when I first
 went into treatment.</i>

22:09.961 --> 22:12.130
Demi was diagnosed bipolar

22:12.163 --> 22:14.066
when she checked into treatment
the first time.

22:15.732 --> 22:17.801
<i> When I got diagnosed
 with bipolar disorder,</i>

22:17.835 --> 22:20.005
it just made sense.

22:22.038 --> 22:24.541
<i> When I was younger,
 I didn't know why</i>

22:24.575 --> 22:26.978
I would stay up so late
writing and playing music.

22:27.010 --> 22:30.414
<i> And then I learned about
 episodes of mania.</i>

22:30.448 --> 22:32.717
And I realized that that's

22:32.750 --> 22:35.953
<i> probably what it was;
 I was manic.</i>

22:35.987 --> 22:38.056
<i> In a way I knew that</i>

22:38.088 --> 22:40.023
it wasn't my fault anymore.

22:40.057 --> 22:42.861
Something was actually off
with me.

22:42.894 --> 22:45.396
Phil: <i>
 She had such a glow to her</i>

22:45.430 --> 22:47.966
<i> the first time I saw her when
 she came out of treatment.</i>

22:47.999 --> 22:51.737
The glow started to fade
each day that passed.

22:53.503 --> 22:54.938
Demi: <i>
 I wasn't working my program,</i>

22:54.971 --> 22:56.607
<i> I wasn't ready to get sober.</i>

22:56.641 --> 23:00.111
<i> I was sneaking it on planes,</i>

23:00.144 --> 23:01.779
<i> sneaking it in bathrooms,</i>

23:01.813 --> 23:02.980
<i> sneaking it throughout
 the night.</i>

23:03.013 --> 23:04.748
Nobody knew.

23:04.781 --> 23:05.849
Phil: <i>
 This is an 18-year-old</i>

23:05.883 --> 23:07.684
<i> who's totally</i>

23:07.718 --> 23:09.120
out-maneuvering adults.

23:09.153 --> 23:11.789
Demi: <i> I went on, like,
 a bender of like</i>

23:11.823 --> 23:14.192
two months where
I was using daily.

23:14.224 --> 23:17.861
<i> And... there was
 one night where</i>

23:17.894 --> 23:20.064
<i> I used a bunch of coke</i>

23:20.096 --> 23:22.500
and I popped a few Xanax bars,

23:22.532 --> 23:25.536
and I started to...
choke a little bit.

23:25.569 --> 23:29.173
<i> And my heart started racing.</i>

23:29.207 --> 23:30.742
<i> And I remember thinking,</i>

23:30.775 --> 23:33.778
"Oh, my God, I might be
overdosing right now."

23:35.212 --> 23:37.147
I remember we were in New York,

23:37.181 --> 23:41.486
<i> and she clearly
 was on something.</i>

23:41.519 --> 23:43.188
<i> And she was on air...</i>

23:43.221 --> 23:45.222
promoting this new way of life.

23:45.256 --> 23:48.560
And I was like,
"You're so full of it."

23:48.593 --> 23:51.229
<i>I wasn't equipped to be able to</i>

23:51.261 --> 23:53.964
<i> handle that situation.</i>

23:53.998 --> 23:57.235
And so I got a list of
several recommendations

23:57.268 --> 23:59.203
of people that
specialize in this.

23:59.237 --> 24:02.673
And I ended up connecting
and speaking with Mike Bayer.

24:02.707 --> 24:04.976
Mike Bayer: <i>
 Demi was on a road to, like,</i>

24:05.009 --> 24:06.743
suicide.

24:06.777 --> 24:08.746
<i> She'd have, like,
 bags of pills,</i>

24:08.778 --> 24:10.080
<i> and an eight-ball of coke.</i>

24:10.114 --> 24:13.518
I was either craving drugs
or on drugs.

24:13.550 --> 24:15.052
She was nasty.

24:15.086 --> 24:17.855
I was not easy to work with.

24:17.888 --> 24:20.657
I was using while I had
a sober companion.

24:20.691 --> 24:23.027
And I went through about 20
different sober companions.

24:23.059 --> 24:25.864
<i> It was really like she was
 two different people.</i>

24:25.896 --> 24:27.965
Every day was like
going to war.

24:27.999 --> 24:30.868
Mike: <i>
 We were in Palm Springs,</i>

24:30.902 --> 24:32.804
<i> and she locked
 her bedroom door,</i>

24:32.836 --> 24:34.204
<i> she's just taken
 a bunch of pills,</i>

24:34.238 --> 24:35.507
<i> we kicked down the door,</i>

24:35.539 --> 24:37.174
<i>she gets taken to the hospital,</i>

24:37.208 --> 24:39.844
the nurse is checking her in,
the bottle of pills is there,

24:39.876 --> 24:43.514
she grabs the pills, she then
downs all the other pills and
says, "You ( bleep ) bitch.

24:43.548 --> 24:46.617
If I just tried to kill myself,
why would you give me
access to pills?"

24:46.651 --> 24:48.620
Demi: <i>
 I didn't feel anything,
 I didn't feel guilty,</i>

24:48.653 --> 24:50.521
<i> I didn't feel embarrassed.</i>

24:50.555 --> 24:52.789
Mike: <i>
 Then she goes from there
 to a psych ward.</i>

24:52.823 --> 24:54.592
<i> None of that did anything.</i>

24:54.625 --> 24:57.161
<i> She still isn't going to
 get clean.</i>

24:57.193 --> 24:59.062
She's so black and white.

24:59.096 --> 25:00.731
She really, one day,
would want to get well,

25:00.765 --> 25:02.033
the next day,
not want to get well.

25:02.066 --> 25:03.567
And when she didn't
want to get well,

25:03.601 --> 25:05.003
she'd have to flip back--
it was just,

25:05.036 --> 25:06.638
for her, it was chaotic.

25:06.671 --> 25:08.640
It was completely exhausting,

25:08.673 --> 25:10.909
<i> physically and emotionally.</i>

25:10.942 --> 25:13.978
I would sneak out, get drugs...

25:14.010 --> 25:15.078
Manipulating.

25:15.112 --> 25:16.314
...I would fake my drugs tests

25:16.346 --> 25:18.215
with other people's pee.

25:18.249 --> 25:20.751
Mike: <i>
 She didn't care
 what the consequences were.</i>

25:20.785 --> 25:22.921
Phil: <i>
 A couple days sober
 and then she'd use.</i>

25:22.953 --> 25:25.123
And I'd lie
straight to their faces.

25:25.155 --> 25:26.957
Mike: <i>
 She didn't care
 about her career.</i>

25:26.990 --> 25:28.792
And we couldn't get
momentum on our side.

