<i> When I was in a relationship
 with Wilmer,</i>

42:33.382 --> 42:36.586
I went three years
without purging.

42:36.619 --> 42:38.654
And when we broke up,

42:38.688 --> 42:41.925
that's one of
the first things I did.

42:41.958 --> 42:43.594
And when I...

42:43.626 --> 42:46.195
feel lonely...

42:46.228 --> 42:47.931
like, my heart feels hungry.

42:47.963 --> 42:49.032
Phil:
Right.

42:49.065 --> 42:50.701
And then I end up binging.

42:52.235 --> 42:54.905
And I don't know
how to figure out...

42:54.938 --> 42:56.307
how to be alone.

43:00.043 --> 43:03.814
What do you think came first
for you in terms of chasing
the high?

43:03.847 --> 43:06.083
Was it the drugs and alcohol
or was it the food?

43:06.115 --> 43:08.085
The food came first.

43:08.117 --> 43:09.619
<i> When I was about
 eight years old</i>

43:09.652 --> 43:11.253
<i> and my little sister was born,</i>

43:11.286 --> 43:13.122
<i> a lot of the attention
 was taken off of me</i>

43:13.155 --> 43:14.657
and onto my little sister.

43:16.726 --> 43:19.061
<i> I had started working
 at that time,</i>

43:19.094 --> 43:21.197
<i>so I was under a lot of stress.</i>

43:21.231 --> 43:24.635
So I would bake cookies
for my family

43:24.668 --> 43:28.172
and I would eat all of them, and
nobody would have any to eat.

43:30.106 --> 43:33.810
<i> That was my first memory
 of food</i>

43:33.842 --> 43:37.714
being... that medicine for me.

43:40.115 --> 43:43.420
<i> When I was 12,</i>

43:43.452 --> 43:45.188
<i> I was bullied.</i>

43:45.221 --> 43:50.027
I... developed a social anxiety

43:50.059 --> 43:53.230
where I didn't trust
other girls my age.

43:53.262 --> 43:58.701
<i> Then, one day, this girl
 who was popular</i>

43:58.735 --> 44:01.938
<i> started saying,
 "Demi should kill herself.</i>

44:01.971 --> 44:04.840
She should slit her wrists."

44:04.873 --> 44:09.245
<i> And it resulted in
 a suicide petition</i>

44:09.278 --> 44:12.715
that got passed around.

44:12.748 --> 44:17.053
And she had other
classmates sign it.

44:17.086 --> 44:20.257
I mean, there was this
core group of girls

44:20.289 --> 44:24.094
who were, honestly, in my eyes,
pure ( bleep ) evil.

44:25.728 --> 44:28.297
Demi: <i>
 And, when I asked them why,</i>

44:28.331 --> 44:30.099
<i> nobody could give me
 a specific reason</i>

44:30.132 --> 44:32.201
why they were treating me
the way they were.

44:33.936 --> 44:35.938
<i> I had no friends,</i>

44:35.972 --> 44:38.375
<i> I was alone.</i>

44:38.407 --> 44:40.911
So I went off of
what they were calling me,

44:40.943 --> 44:45.882
which was a whore and being fat.

44:45.914 --> 44:48.217
<i> I called my mom on my cell
 phone and I said, "I'm done,</i>

44:48.251 --> 44:49.987
<i> I can't do this anymore,
 pick me up.</i>

44:52.222 --> 44:54.091
She picked me up from school

44:54.123 --> 44:56.292
and that's when my eating
disorder developed.

44:58.862 --> 45:00.463
<i> One day,</i>

45:00.496 --> 45:04.300
I found a copy of her diary.

45:04.333 --> 45:08.504
<i> Demi had drawn a picture of
 what she perceived herself</i>

45:08.538 --> 45:10.306
to look like.

45:12.074 --> 45:13.843
"Heavy."

45:13.876 --> 45:15.911
And then she drew a picture
on the next page,

45:15.945 --> 45:19.316
and said, "This is what
I need to look like

45:19.349 --> 45:21.284
<i> to be...</i>

45:21.317 --> 45:23.019
a star."

45:23.052 --> 45:26.990
This was, like,
a collage that I made

45:27.023 --> 45:30.026
when I was younger.

45:30.059 --> 45:32.028
And it's actually kind of sad
for me because

45:32.061 --> 45:36.133
a lot of the people in here
are underweight and...

45:36.166 --> 45:38.535
I wanted to be so much...

45:38.568 --> 45:41.338
I wanted to be like them.

45:41.371 --> 45:44.840
<i> That was kind of the chic look
 back then.</i>

45:44.873 --> 45:47.409
Yeah, I've got Amy Winehouse
in there that I looked up to

45:47.443 --> 45:49.413
and I wanted to be so badly.

45:52.114 --> 45:54.850
<i> I wanted to be as thin as her,
 I wanted to sing like her,</i>

45:54.884 --> 45:57.086
I wanted to be just like her.

45:59.121 --> 46:02.158
<i> The collages on her wall,
 and the pictures,</i>

46:02.192 --> 46:03.492
and the models,

46:03.525 --> 46:05.861
<i> this isn't what you need to</i>

46:05.894 --> 46:08.264
<i> aspire to be like,
 this is not healthy.</i>

46:08.297 --> 46:10.399
I never thought to say
those things to her

46:10.432 --> 46:13.135
because I didn't know myself.

46:13.168 --> 46:15.237
<i> My desire for perfection,</i>

46:15.271 --> 46:16.539
I think I've always
been that way.

46:16.572 --> 46:20.342
<i> But I felt I had to be thin</i>

46:20.376 --> 46:22.512
<i> to be beautiful,
 and successful,</i>

46:22.545 --> 46:25.282
<i> and that this is what you
 need to look like</i>

46:25.315 --> 46:28.083
<i> in order to be perfect.</i>

46:28.117 --> 46:31.054
I may have passed that
along to my kids,

46:31.086 --> 46:33.556
<i> that wanting everything
 to be perfect,</i>

46:33.590 --> 46:36.526
<i> and need to be</i>

46:36.559 --> 46:39.863
thin and beautiful
to be successful.

46:39.896 --> 46:42.332
Demi: <i>
 Food is still the biggest
 challenge in my life</i>

46:42.364 --> 46:45.968
and it controls...

46:46.001 --> 46:47.503
I don't want to give it
the power to say that

46:47.536 --> 46:50.039
it controls my every thought,

46:50.072 --> 46:54.476
<i> but... it's something that
 I'm constantly thinking about.</i>

46:54.510 --> 46:58.348
<i> Body image,
 what I'm gonna eat next,</i>

46:58.380 --> 47:00.951
<i> what I wish I could be eating,</i>

47:00.983 --> 47:02.918
what I wish I didn't eat.

47:02.952 --> 47:04.287
You know, it's just constant.

47:04.320 --> 47:06.556
It's exhausting.

47:06.588 --> 47:08.391
<i> Like, I get envious towards</i>

47:08.423 --> 47:13.329
<i> people that don't struggle
 with an eating disorder</i>

47:13.362 --> 47:14.364
<i> just because I feel like</i>

47:14.396 --> 47:18.235
my life would be so much easier.

47:18.268 --> 47:20.336
<i> Everybody has their own path
 in recovery.</i>

47:20.369 --> 47:23.072
<i> For me, it's about going to
 therapy, working my program</i>

47:23.106 --> 47:25.375
<i> and having an honest
 relationship with myself</i>

47:25.407 --> 47:27.143
<i>and the other people around me.</i>

47:27.175 --> 47:31.514
I had come across Jay Glazer
and Unbreakable Gym.

47:31.547 --> 47:35.952
<i> And I felt like it would be
 great for her.</i>

47:35.985 --> 47:39.256
Because Demi had just broken up
with Wilmer

47:39.289 --> 47:41.925
<i> and she didn't have
 a lot of friendships,</i>

47:41.958 --> 47:44.059
<i> she didn't have a community.</i>

47:44.092 --> 47:45.661
The workout before that
was super tough.

47:45.695 --> 47:48.064
- Yeah.
- You hear a girl crying,
  it's me.

